url_description: A federal judge says a Mexican drug cartel accused in the gruesome killings of nine women and children from an offshoot Mormon community must pay $1.5 billion to the families. The award determined by U.S. Magistrate Judge Clare Hochhalter of North Dakota will be automatically tripled under federal Anti-Terrorism Act, increasing the amount to $4.6 billion. Several surviving family members have been working in North Dakota.
